esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when deployment available/desired replica ratio drops below 1.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// AVG(available) / AVG(desired) < 1 means some replicas are unavailable.
//
// What it means:
// Deployment not fully running — reduced capacity or degraded service.
//
// Common causes:
// Image pull errors, resource constraints, scheduling failures, crash loops.
//
// Handles division by zero: filters out deployments with zero desired replicas.
TS metrics-kubernetes.state_deployment-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.deployment.replicas.available` IS NOT NULL
| STATS
    avg_available = AVG(`kubernetes.deployment.replicas.available`),
    avg_desired = AVG(`kubernetes.deployment.replicas.desired`)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.deployment.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE avg_desired IS NOT NULL AND avg_desired > 0
| EVAL availability_ratio = ROUND(avg_available / avg_desired, 4)
| WHERE availability_ratio < 1
